# Authority OS — Flow + Pulse Design System

**Status:** Flow shipped (Codex Task 9). Pulse layer is next.

---

## Overview

Authority OS uses a **dual-layer visual system**. These two layers are not interchangeable — they have separate roles, separate colors, and a strict hierarchy.

| Layer | Role | Emotional Outcome |
|---|---|---|
| **Flow** | Primary UI shell — daily usability and feel | Calm, controlled, easy to engage with |
| **Pulse** | Intelligence overlay — insight and context signals | Informed, aware, improving |

**Rule:** Flow dominates visually. Pulse enhances meaning. Pulse must never overpower Flow.

---

## Layer 1 — Flow (Primary Experience)

### Identity
Flow makes the product feel natural, fluid, and usable every day. It's the fintech shell users interact with constantly. Inspired by Chime/Cash App but more refined and systemized.

### Color Tokens (live in `src/index.css`)

| Token | Value | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg-base` | `#07130F` | App shell / page background |
| `--color-bg-surface` | `#0D1F19` | Card background |
| `--color-bg-raised` | `#123027` | Elevated surfaces, button hover |
| `--color-bg-gradient` | `linear-gradient(180deg, #0F2A21, #07130F)` | Header / container zones |
| `--color-accent-primary` | `#00C896` | Primary CTAs, active states, highlights |
| `--color-accent-soft` | `#4ADE80` | Soft positive indicators |
| `--color-gold` | `#00C896` | Legacy alias — maps to accent-primary |
| `--color-green` | `#22C55E` | Semantic success |
| `--color-red` | `#EF4444` | Semantic danger |
| `--color-warning` | `#F59E0B` | Semantic warning |
| `--color-text-primary` | `#E6F4EF` | Body text |
| `--color-text-secondary` | `#7FA39A` | Labels, sublabels |
| `--color-text-disabled` | `#4A645C` | Inactive / disabled |
| `--color-border-subtle` | `#1F3B31` | Card borders |
| `--color-border-accent` | `rgba(0,200,150,0.28)` | Accent-highlighted borders |

### Typography
- Headings: Inter (or General Sans)
- Body: Inter
- Mono: JetBrains Mono (inputs and data table cells only)
- Style: clean hierarchy, large numeric emphasis for metrics, open spacing

### Component Style
- Cards: floating, rounded (12–16px), soft shadows, minimal borders
- Layout: grid-based, 12px gap, 20px section margins
- Spacing: more breathing room than dense dashboards

### Motion Rules
- Transitions: smooth, ease-in-out — motion feels like flow, not reward
- No bounce, no arcade effects, no scale-up on mount
- Press state: `scale(0.97)` only
- All durations ≤ 500ms (except countup at 1200ms)
- Entrance stagger: `fadeSlideUp` 400ms, 80ms/card delay, capped at 400ms

### What to Avoid
- neon green overload or Cash App clone feel
- loud gradients or banding
- overly flat design (needs depth)
- gamified motion or reward feedback
- rigid enterprise table layouts

